description.narrative: UNICEF continued its support to the Government of Sao Tome e Principe along with its development partners to implement the Youth Action Plan 2020-2024 that prioritize development, empowerment and employment of youth as part of the national development agenda. Despite the challenges imposed by COVID, activities were implemented enabling skills development of youth and adolescents, leaving them better prepared to identify and propose solutions to problems affecting them such as early pregnancy, HIV, alcohol abuse, risky behaviours.; To this end, the capacity of partners was strengthened to promote youth engagement, life skills training and awareness raising campaigns. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:26/01/2022
